Abdomen
brown with tergites from 2 onwards yellow apically, narrowly on 2, apical third on 3, apical half on 4–5, more narrowly on shorter tergites 6–7, 8 all brownish; genitalia and sternites brownish yellow; all bristling dark. 
Genitalia
(
Figs 6–8
) with widely separated gonocoxites having only membranous connection; gonostylus simple, narrowed and outwardly pointed apically; aedeagus (
Fig. 7
) broad and robust, longer than gonocoxites. Tergite 9 (
Fig. 8
) broad but narrowed medially, small densely bristled cerci protruding from apical emargination.

Chorotype. Type 6 [3.02 of
Vigna Taglianti et al. (1999)
]. Mediterranean.
